translated:
Engström, Bror Gösta Allan, dentist, Alingsås, b. 12/3/02 in Nårunga, Älvsborgs län, son of elementary school teacher Carl Albert E. and Anna Sofia Johansson. Married on 29th with Berta Cederberg. Children: Ulla-Britt b. 31. - High school diploma in Skara 23, dentist degree 25, licensed dentist 27. Temporary work in Skara 27-28, practice in Alingsås since 28. 

Engström, Einar Berthold Theodore, rector, Norrköping, b. 15/10/84 in Gothenburg, son of headmaster August E. and Bertha Wallgren. Married 1. in 12 with Gudrun Olsson, died 18; 2. in 20 with Anna Nordenberg. Children: Rolf b. 13, d. 39, Gerd b. 16. - Master's degree from Gothenburg's high school in Latin 03, Bachelor's in Philosophy in Gothenburg 07, Licentiate in Philosophy 10, PhD in Philosophy 11, intern at Gothenburg's high school in Latin 14. Doctor in Latin at Gothenburg's University 11-16, appointed to partially maintain lecturing duties in Latin 12, 13, and 14. Hourly teacher at Gothenburg's Girls' Gymnasium 05-16, teacher at Gothenburg's Private School 11-16, lecturer in Latin and Greek at Karlstad's Higher Primary School since 16, at the northern Latin in Stockholm since 31, rector at Norrköping's Higher Primary School since 26. Studied the rector of Karlstad's elementary school for girls from 21-26. In Karlstad, among other things, served as Press Freedom Representative 17-26, acted as a board member in the Food Committee 18-19, substitute in the Budget Committee 19-26, chairman of the Red Cross War Children's Committee in Värmland 20-22, town councilor (conservative) and chairman in the Wage Committee 21-26, town councilor in Norrköping since 30, church councilor during the same time, board chairman in Norrköping System A-B and the Östra Sweden Allm. Restaurant A-B, inspector in Norrköping's vocational education institution. Traveled to Germany, Austria, Italy, and France in 09, 10, 12, 31 and 39. Written works: Commentary on the Roman Regional Catalog (10), Garmina Latina Epigraphica (11). RNO,  Officer of the Order of the Polar Star, Royal Order of the Sword with King Gustaf V's portrait, Commander of the Order of Vasa with King Gustaf V's portrait, and 2nd and 3rd class of P. R. K. M.
